<title type="html"><![CDATA[Sirah &amp; Biographies • Shaikh ul-Islām Imām Sufyān Bin Saʿīd ath-Thawrī]]></title>

<category term="Sirah &amp; Biographies" scheme="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewforum.php?f=14" label="Sirah &amp; Biographies"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1572&amp;p=1692#p1692"><![CDATA[
Shaikh ul-Islām Imām Sufyān Bin Saʿīd ath-Thawrī <br /><br />Born 97 Hijrī<br />Died 163 Hijrī<br /><br />His Kunyāh was Abū ʿAbdullāh. <br /><br />Imām adh-Dhahabī said,<br /><br /><strong>&quot;He was a brilliant, illustrious, renowned and eminent Faqīh and master of Hifdh who lived in Kūfah.&quot;</strong><br /><br />Imām Yahya Bin Saʿīd al-Qattān said,<br /><br /><strong>&quot;I have not seen anyone who is greater and has memorised more Hadīth than him.&quot;</strong><br /><br />Imām Awzaʿī said,<br /><br /><strong>&quot;There is no person that has remained where the whole Ummāh has an Ijmā that they are likeable and have precise authentic Hadith except for Imām Sufyān ath-Thawrī.&quot;</strong><br /><br />Imām Ibn ul-Mūbārak said,<br /><br /><strong>&quot;I do not know of anyone on the face of this earth who has more knowledge than Imām Sufyān ath-Thawrī.&quot;</strong><br /><br />Imām Wakīʿ said,<br /><br /><strong>&quot;Imām Sufyān ath-Thawrīs knowledge was as great as the sea. I have not seen anyone in the whole of ʿIrāq who has the same amount of knowledge and virtue than Imām Sufyān ath-Thawrī.&quot;<br /></strong><br /><em>(Tadhkiratul Huffādh volume 1, page no.172, 173)</em><br /><br /><em>Translated by Abu Ubaydah </em><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=59">Abu Ubaydah</a> — Thu Apr 23, 2020 3:15 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
